title: calculating
text: calculate_allocation() function determines allocate samples based desired number samples (nSamp) input sraster. function used internally number functions, including sample_strat. Currently, three methods allocations included: proportional (prop; default), optimal (optim), equal (equal), manual (manual) allocation. Proportional - Samples allocated based coverage area strata. default allocation method. Optimal - Samples allocated based variation within strata. Equal - number samples ( defined nSamp) allocated strata. Manual - Numeric vector weights provided allowing users manually assign weights strata.

text: sample_nc() function implements Nearest Centroid sampling algorithm described Melville & Stone (2016). algorithm uses kmeans clustering number clusters (centroids) equal desired number samples (nSamp). Cluster centers located, prompts nearest neighbour mraster pixel cluster located (assuming default k parameter). nearest neighbours output samples. Basic usage follows:  Altering k parameter leads multiplicative increase output samples total output samples = \(`nSamp` * `k`\).  Visualizing kmeans centers samples nearest neighbours looks like possible using details = TRUE. $kplot output provides quick visualization centers based scatter plot first 2 layers mraster. Notice centers well distributed covariate space chosen samples closest pixels center (nearest neighbours).

text: sample_clhs() function implements conditioned Latin hypercube (clhs) sampling methodology clhs package. number functions sgsR package help provide guidance clhs sampling including calculate_pop() calculate_lhsOpt(). Check functions better understand sample numbers optimized. syntax function similar others shown , although parameters like iter, define number iterations within Metropolis-Hastings process important consider. examples use low iter value takes less time run. Default values iter within clhs package 10,000.   cost parameter defines mraster covariate, used constrain clhs sampling. number variables. example distance pixel road access (e.g. calculate_distance() see example ), terrain slope, output calculate_coobs(), many others.
code: sample_clhs(mraster = mraster, # input             nSamp = 200, # desired sample number             plot = TRUE, # plot              iter = 100) # number of iterations sample_clhs(mraster = mraster, # input             nSamp = 300, # desired sample number             iter = 100, # number of iterations             existing = existing, # existing samples             access = access, # define access road network             buff_inner = 100, # inner buffer - no samples within this distance from road             buff_outer = 300, # outer buffer - no samples further than this distance from road             plot = TRUE) # plot #--- cost constrained examples ---# #--- calculate distance to access layer for each pixel in mr ---# mr.c <- calculate_distance(raster = mraster, # input                            access = access,                            plot = TRUE) # define access road network sample_clhs(mraster = mr.c, # input             nSamp = 250, # desired sample number             iter = 100, # number of iterations             cost = "dist2access", # cost parameter - name defined in calculate_distance()             plot = TRUE) # plot

title: sgsR
text: sgsR primarily scripted using tidyverse, terra package handle raster processing, sf package vector manipulation. Currently, 4 primary function verbs package uses: strat_* - Stratify verb directs functions apply stratification algorithms input metrics raster mraster produce stratified raster sraster output. sample_* - Sample verb directs functions extract samples srasters, produced strat_* functions. algorithms (sample_srs(), sample_balanced(), sample_systematic()) capable using mrasters input algorithms depend stratified inputs sampling. calculate_* - Calculate verb directs functions perform calculations; values derived calculations used subsequent processing. Predefined sample analysis algorithms (calculate_representation(), calculate_coobs()) included. extract_* - Derive raster data co-located sample. Includes extract_metrics() deriving mraster data, extract_strata() deriving stratum srasters. functions used internally within sgsR.

title: stratification
text: strat_quantiles() algorithm divides data equally sized strata (nStrata). Similar strat_breaks() function, (quantile) algorithm capability perform stratification single mraster; users can also input secondary mraster (mraster2) specify number associated desired strata (nStrata2). title: sgsR: Structurally Guided Sampling — sgsR-package
text: Structurally guided sampling (SGS) approaches airborne laser scanning (ALS; LIDAR). Primary functions provide means generate data-driven stratifications & methods allocating samples. Intermediate functions calculating extracting important information input covariates samples also included. Processing outcomes intended help forest environmental management practitioners better optimize field sample placement well assess augment existing sample networks context data distributions conditions. ALS data primary intended use case, however rasterized remote sensing data can used, enabling data-driven stratifications sampling approaches.

title: sgsR 1.3.1
text: CRAN release: 2022-10-14 fixed - sample_systematic() added random translation sampling grid ensure unbiased sampling.

title: sgsR 1.3.0
text: new - sample_existing() added. algorithm sub-samples existing sample using internal latin hypercube sampling. Constraints form cost parameter akin sample_clhs() exist. Sub-sampling can performed existing samples alone, using population level mraster distributions. new - mask_existing() - internal function masking exising samples using access buffers.

title: sgsR 1.2.1
text: fixed - sample_systematic() bug cellsize values caused samples intersect raster cause extract_metrics() provide error existing samples. Added check intersection corresponding error message. enhancement - Added quiet extract_metrics() & extract_strata() allow internal use without messages.

title: sgsR 1.2.0
text: CRAN release: 2022-08-07 fixed - strat_kmeans() bug related terra re-assignment values output raster causing issues. R Hijmans kindly suggested edit made. fixed - sample_ahels() - bug extra attributes existing cause algorithm crash re-merging sampling. fixed - strat_quantiles() longer plots histogram / scatter plot using plot = TRUE. Now correctly adds details list details = TRUE. new sampling method - Added sample_nc() based algorithm described Melville & Stone (2016) algorithm uses kmeans clustering number clusters equal desired number samples. Cluster centers located, prompts nearest neighbour raster pixel cluster located (assuming default k parameter). nearest neighbours output samples. Visualization centers samples can dispayed details = TRUE used $kplot plotted. fixed - sample_systematic() now inherent randomness lower left corner tessellation. fixed - strat_kmeans() solved issue first raster layer involved stratification.

title: sgsR 1.1.0
text: enhanced - sample_strat() - added parameter method allows users choose "Queinnec" (default method implemented previous sgsR versions) "random" (stratified random sampling). random method ignores much functionality algorithm allow users use standard stratified random sampling approaches without use focal window locate contiguous stratum cells. fixed - sample_strat() factor handling improvement - GitHub issue #18 enhanced - calculate_allocation() improved documentation output data frame make attributes clear. fixed - calculate_representation() now plot bar chart twice & NA values existing removed. fixed - existing samples attributes now break sampling using sample_ahels() / sample_clhs() values NA. Variables also added back sample output

title: sgsR 1.0.0
text: CRAN release: 2022-06-24 First CRAN release.

title: sgsR 0.1.6
text: Added comprehensive tests using testthat functions covr reporting. Resulting tests: miscellaneous adjustments many functions including small non-critical bug fixed, error message improvements. Changed forceSamp force sample_systematic(). Removed details sample_coob(). Improved ability use data.frames() samples inputs numerous algorithms. Improve consistency error messages call. = FALSE across package. Added existingna.shp example data point NA locations.

title: sgsR 0.1.5
text: strat_map() can now map categorical srasters (gave error ). Now also returns categories associated categorical rasters lookup table details = TRUE. Altered error handling raster masking within mask_access() instead individual sampling functions. Changes terra::distance() & terra::classify() required slight modifications calculate_distance() strat_breaks() sample_strat strat_rule1() strat_rule2() functions make code concise. Fixed issue mindist setting distances strata. sample_ahels() Added tolerance parameter sample_ahels() allow users define tolerance around desired sampling ratio (max tolerance =  0.1). allow user say “ideally want ratio XX ’m OK ratio XX - threshold means don’t need add samples”. Fix issue error occurred existing data frame. sample_ahels made ahels_nSamp() ahels_threshold() functions make code concise. Altered existing (crosses) new (circles) samples plotted sample_strat() sample_ahels(). Added internal utility functions allocate_prop / allocate_optim / allocate_manual / allocate_equal / allocate_existing / allocate_force integrated calculate_allocation() make code succinct purposeful.

title: sgsR 0.1.4
text: Fixed issue calculate_allocation() many samples allocated (compared user-defined nSamp) due using ceiling() instead round() proportional optimal allocation. Added allocation = "manual" calculate_allocation(). parameter weights added (mandatory allocation = "manual"), users can provide numeric vector relative weightings strata. sum(weights) must equal 1. Added weights parameter sample_strat() allow "manual" allocation. Allow buff_inner NULL providing access isolate samples. allows users define maximum distance (wish ) samples can access specify minimum distance.

title: sgsR 0.1.3
text: Updates names internal package data inst/exdata corresponding examples vignettes. Added contingencies sample_ahels, sample_strat, calculate_allocation, calculate_coobs allow existing samples fall areas NA cause algorithms fail bug. extract_metrics & extract_strata produce robust error messages & now generate message existing samples co-located strata metric values NA. sample_clhs updated fix issue existing samples appended output. strat_quantiles now provides stratum look-table details = TRUE allow user see exact metric break points. Updated documentation many algorithms fix grammatical spelling errors.

title: sgsR 0.1.2
text: Removed dependencies stringr, tidyselect, rlang, RColorBrewer, magrittr, glue, Rcpp. Improved documentation examples read speeds line <5 seconds CRAN submission. Improve processing speed sample_coobs() utils-mat.R courtesy Jean-Romain Roussel. Added example subset file inst/extdata improve example processing speeds certain algorithms.
